default&#xa0; 
defaultThe BBC’s governance model beyond 2016 will be considered as part of Charter Review and we do not wish to pre
default-
defaultjudge that process. 
defaultOur priority is to make the existing model work as effectively as possible, within the constraints 
defaultof the current Charter. 
default&#xa0;
default59.
default&#xa0; 
defaultIn September
default 2013
default, 
defaultthe Trust and Executive 
defaultannounced 
defaulta joint 
defaultreview 
defaultof 
defaultthe BBC’s internal governance systems and structures, and the culture that surrounds them. We did this in response to a number of events that prompted legitimate questions about the effectiveness of the BBC’s system of governance, both within and between t
defaulthe Trust and Executive. 
default&#xa0;
default60.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe 
defaultoutcome of the 
defaultreview, announced on 11
defaultth
default December
default, is that the respective responsibilities of the Trust and Executive Board will be clarified, within the terms of the Charter. The Trust will focus on its oversight and regulat
defaultory role, ensuring we are answerable to licence fee payers.
default&#xa0;
default The Executive will be responsible for running the organisation. 
default&#xa0;
default61.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe role of the Executive Board will be strengthened.
default&#xa0;
default It will be responsible for all aspects of management and operations and th
defaulte main decision-making forum for the 
defaultBBC.
default&#xa0;
default The role and number of non-executive directors on the 
defaultExecutive Board 
defaultwill increase, starting with the appointment of Sir Howard Stringer, previously CEO and chairman of Sony, from January 2014. We will also reduc
defaulte the number of pan-BBC boards by more than 60%. 
default&#xa0;
default62.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThese changes are designe
defaultd to deliver simpler 
defaultstructures, bet
defaultter decision-making and proper 
defaultaccountability.
default&#xa0;
default They 
defaultshould 
defaultensure everyone in
defaultside and outside the BBC is 
defaultclear about who is responsible for 
defaultmajor decisions and projects. The BBC should also be able to make faster decisions and reduce the time senior managers spend in meetings and increase the time spent making output for audiences.
