default&#xa0;
default64.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe Charter model underpins the BBC’s unique governance structure and funding model, explicitly committing the Government of the day to respect the editorial and operational independence of the BBC. Charter terms are subject to extensive political d
defaulteba
defaultte at the time of Charter review
default, ensuring appropriate parliamentary and public scrutiny, but 
defaultwith a 
defaultrelatively fixed period to provide room for the BBC to deliver on its commitments. The ten-year 
defaultterm gives the BBC a sufficient horizon over which to pl
defaultan investment and helps to keep decisions on the BBC’s remit out-of-step with the electoral cycle. The Charter also has a symbolic value, we believe, emphasising for the UK public and stakeholders the special role and responsibilities which the BBC has as 
defaultan independent broadcaster and trusted national institution.
